File: An electric board. Pixabay/Taken/711 JOHANNESBURG -  Eskom will be implementing load reduction in Free State, Gauteng and KwaZulu-Natal on Monday, to avoid network overloading in high-density areas. The power utility said load reduction will take place between 5pm and 10pm. READ: Eskom fraud case postponed to June Areas like Ivory Park, Soweto, Msunduzi, Ladysmith and Msinga will be affected by the load reduction. Provincial statements issued by Eskom name the specific areas that will be experiencing power cuts. Eskom Load Reduction Notice
